<br>
I've been to ToV several times with a different guild,  and am attempting to explain the MT/keep agro/max melee range concepts.   I was wondering if anyone saw any guides out there for these tactics which obviously make/break raids  (and certain kills).<br>
<br>
So far I've got:<br>
- one tank keeping agro means that the clerics only have to heal one person not a bunch of people.<br>
- maxmeelee range helps to keep agro on the MT<br>
- BT is the only other one becides MT that should be taunting (to transition to BT faster should the MT die)<br>
- MT is the one that is ALWAYS assisted unless we have multiple non-mezzable ads then everyone goes to the BT's mob while the MT starts tanking a new mob.<br>
- Everone behind the mob at all times (thinking on changing this to only when mob is eraged)<br>
- Sarifice your Damage per sec in favor of the mob not beating on you.<br>
- Don't pingpong; people that need to debuff the mob stand becide the MT so he can continue to taunt non-stop instead of chasing after you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufuloriancavestomper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FulorianCavestomper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Smithing Guru</span><br>  Posts: 954<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/24/02 6:58:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1305.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Looking for a good guide to aggro/MT...</span><hr size=1> Nothing in HoT is even remotely mezzable. <p><img src="http://strike9.com/eq/file.aspx/path=/Fulorian/fullsize/sig1.gif" border="0">
