<br>
In hot you need to pay attention to the type of mobs pulled/added and adjust accordingly.<br>
<br>
For example, if your main tank is busy on a wurm, and a vehement wyvern comes along... Dont bet on your ST staying alive for more than 8 seconds (Im assuming your tanks are between 5500 to 6000 buffed if just starting HoT) if your healers are not paying close attention.  Those are nasty, usually are one of the roamers and require /disc defen many times and can whipe out a raid fast.  A single tank / cleric tank mezzing one of those will not last too long (guessing on your current capabilities). <br>
<br>
The other thing you need to tell your healers on adds is to make sure the tanks at the time do not drop below 40% health or so when you have multiple mobs.  They will get low health aggro and get summoned / chewed real fast.<br>
